  "body": "I understand the reason a `requirements.yaml` uses the repo URL as the canonical location identifier. That seems like a good idea. I was surprised however when packaging a chart on a CI server that `helm repo add <name> <url>` must also be done before a subchart on a public repo can be used.\r\n\r\nSteps to reproduce:\r\n\r\n### requirements.yaml\r\n```yaml\r\ndependencies:\r\n  - name: cert-manager\r\n    version: v0.9.0-alpha.0\r\n    repository: https://charts.jetstack.io\r\n```\r\n### actual\r\n```\r\n$ helm package charts/my-chart --dependency-update\r\nError: no repository definition for https://charts.jetstack.io. Please add them via 'helm repo add'\r\n```\r\n### expected\r\nbehavior of `--dependency-update` and `helm dependency update` to be more like `helm fetch`, which does not require `helm repo add` or `helm repo update` to be done.\r\n```\r\n$ helm fetch cert-manager --repo https://charts.jetstack.io --version v0.9.0-alpha.0 --destination charts/my-chart/charts\r\n$ ls charts/my-chart/charts\r\ncert-manager-v0.9.0-alpha.0.tgz\r\n```",
